  "prompt": "How do I date a friend?",
  "response": "Dating a friend can be tricky, but here are some tips:\n\n1. Assess your feelings\n- Are you genuinely interested in a romantic relationship?\n- Consider potential risks to your friendship\n\n2. Evaluate compatibility\n- Do you share similar values and goals?\n- Are you emotionally compatible?\n\n3. Gauge their interest\n- Look for signs they might be interested\n- Have subtle conversations about relationships\n- Pay attention to their body language\n\n4. Have an honest conversation\n- Choose a comfortable, private setting\n- Express your feelings clearly\n- Be prepared for potential rejection\n- Emphasize that you value the friendship\n\n5. Take it slow\n- Don't rush into a relationship\n- Maintain friendship dynamics\n- Communicate openly about expectations\n\n6. Consider potential consequences\n- Be prepared that the friendship might change\n- Discuss how you'll handle potential breakup\n- Have a plan to preserve the friendship\n\n7. Communicate effectively\n- Be honest about your feelings\n- Listen to their perspective\n- Respect their response\n\n8. If they're not interested\n- Accept their decision gracefully\n- Give them space if needed\n- Continue valuing the friendship\n\nRemember, every situation is unique, and there's no guaranteed approach.\n\nWould you like more specific advice about your situation?",
